## This file is automatically generated from /etc/audit/rules.d
# Exclude-overlap suppression (f3 section 3.5, catalog #32). An exclude-list rule
# filters out a whole record TYPE (msgtype); here it suppresses CWD records that the
# watch below would otherwise emit as part of its event group. The exclude REDUCES
# net bytes where it overlaps the watch's scope; it never adds. Direction suppressive.
#
# Exclude rule: drop all CWD records (a per-event sub-record, ~60 B each, f3 section 3.2).
-a always,exclude -F msgtype=CWD
# Watch: write/attr access to /etc (recursive subtree, f3 section 2.2). HIGH.
-w /etc -p wa -k etc_changes
